Name can change on rebirth. Though religion usually stays th=
e same, it CAN change. Nationality can of course change too. Job, skills, e=
xternal nature, looks, gender, even yoni (human, cow, goat, chicken, tiger =
etc) can all change from birth to birth.
 
Basically, the seed of one's new=
 birth is formed at the time of one's death. As one's connection is severed=
 with the body, the last desires/thoughts/ponderings of the mind become the=
 seed for the next life. Nature chooses for one a future course that allows=
 one to pursue those desires, as much as allowed by one's previous karmas a=
nd debts.
 
If one is able to not entertain ANY desire as one element after=
 another evaporates in one's existence, one becomes liberated. All the spir=
itual sadhana we do is a dress rehearsal.
 
