When it comes to recognizing the rebirth of a great soul, it can become =
a trap.
 
Ramakrishna explicitly told Sarada Mata that he would be back aft=
er 100 years and that everybody else who came with him would have to come b=
ack with him. When Sarada Mata and Lakshmi Devi protested, he said they did=
 not have a choice! Even Swami Vivekananda said once in USA, "I have to com=
e back once more. The Master said I am to come back once more with him". Wh=
en questioned "you have to come back because Shri Ramakrishna says so", he =
replied, "souls like that have great power, Madam". On another occasion, Ra=
makrishna said that people would get liberated en masse during his next com=
ing and that would be the last opportunity for a long time to come.
 
Inter=
estingly, two good saints claimed to be re-incarnations of Ramakrishna sinc=
e then. One of them is wrong (or perhaps both!). Another good saint suggest=
ed that she is the re-incarnation of Sarada Mata. Satya Sai Baba said that =
he identified a particular young man as the reincarnation of Swami Vivekana=
nda. Ramakrishna was surrounded by Sarada Mata and more than twenty discipl=
es of a very high caliber and different aptitudes. Together, they nearly mo=
ulded the direction of spiritual India for the next century. None of the cl=
aimants of rebirthhood are surrounded by people of such caliber or fit the =
bill.
 
Thus, there can be false claimants to the rebirthhood of a great so=
ul! It is not that they are lying. They may simply be deluding themselves a=
nd of course ego is the root of delusion!
 
